OL,3,CVictim's children voice fears as
OL,4,Creview of murderer's release moves
OL,5,Cforward
OL,7,FThe children of a woman killed by a
OL,8,Fmurderer serving a whole-life sentence
OL,9,Fhave warned he "poses a clear and
OL,10,Fpresent threat to the public" as
OL,11,Fdiscussions on his release move to the
OL,12,Fnext stage.
OL,14,FVictor Farrant was jailed for life at
OL,15,Fin 1998 for the murder of former
OL,16,Fgirlfriend Glenda Hoskins, 44, and the
OL,17,Fattempted murder of Ann Fidler, 45.
OL,19,FSentencing him, Mr Justice Butterfield
OL,20,Fsaid that he was so dangerous that he
OL,21,Fshould "never be released".
